 Police in Kiambu rescued a 38-year old man from being
lynched after he allegedly attempted to rape a woman in Githunguri on Tuesday
night. According to the Directorate of Criminal Investigation (DCI) statement, the suspect, Peter Kariuki waylaid the victim at Nyaga village as
she returned home from Kwa Maiko
shopping center, and attempted to rape her. The woman
wrestled her way out as she cried for help an act that attracted passer-by who came
to her aid and cornered the perpetrator. “In a matter of minutes before standby police officers from Ngewa station could arrive at the
scene, Kariuki had been turned into a punching bag, with responders serving him
an overdose of mighty blows and hot slaps to instill some manners,” DCI stated. The police
arrived on time to save Kariuki and he was rushed to Ngewa Health Centre
where he was treated and discharged. DCI further noted
that a Lenovo phone belonging to the victim was recovered after
searching the suspect.  The suspect is behind bars awaiting arraignment.